WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:05.268
Responses to challenges are heavily dictated by personal values. Values

00:00:05.268 --> 00:00:10.536
are individually internalized attitudes about what is right, wrong, ethical,

00:00:10.536 --> 00:00:15.804
and moral. They heavily influence perceptions of problems and preferences.

00:00:15.804 --> 00:00:21.072
Challenges often lack simplistic answers, and an internal code of

00:00:21.072 --> 00:00:26.340
ethics determines how power is exercised. The Congruence Gravity Model

00:00:26.340 --> 00:00:31.608
explains this simply. First, you have values. Second, you have

00:00:31.608 --> 00:00:36.876
beliefs. Third, you have actions. When thoughts, feelings, and behaviors

00:00:36.876 --> 00:00:42.144
align with genuineness and honesty towards others, congruence is achieved.

00:00:42.144 --> 00:00:47.412
Congruence grounds leadership in values, provides stability for the team,

00:00:47.412 --> 00:00:52.680
allows others to predict actions, and fundamentally builds shared trust.
